Type: Package
Package: nanoAFMr
Title: Load and Analyze Atomic Force Microscopy Data Files
Version: 2.3.1
Author: Thomas Gredig [aut, cre, cph] (<https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5824-7626>)
Authors@R: 
    person("Thomas", "Gredig", , "tgredig@csulb.edu", 
          role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-5824-7626"))
Maintainer: Thomas Gredig <tgredig@csulb.edu>
Description: Import and graph atomic force microscopy (AFM) image files 
    for analysis. The supported file formats include NanoSurf NID
    files, Bruker and VEECO NanoScope files, Park AFM files, and Asylum 
    Research Igor wavefiles. It supports image flattening, height-height 
    correlation function analysis, line profiles, and other basic data analysis. 
    It supports analysis of spectroscopy data for Park AFM files. This material is based 
    upon work supported by the National Science Foundation under Grant Number 2018653. 
    Any opinions, findings, and conclusions or recommendations expressed in 
    this material are those of the author and do not necessarily reflect 
    the views of the National Science Foundation.
